headline: Did Analyst Optimism on Lending and Revenue Growth Just Shift KeyCorp’s (KEY) Investment Narrative?
summary: Earlier this week, anticipation grew around KeyCorp’s upcoming third-quarter results, as analysts projected significant earnings and revenue growth driven by improved lending and strong net interest income, alongside an expected boost from non-interest income in mortgage banking and investment banking. Analyst expectations for KeyCorp to surpass consensus earnings estimates highlight growing confidence in the company’s ability to maintain resilient asset quality and capitalize on stable...
